<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 5:53PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
northwestern Bath County through 615 PM EDT...
At 553 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lake Moomaw, or 8 miles northwest of Hot Springs, moving northeast at
50 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Lake Moomaw...
and Mountain Grove.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
